{
  "doc_id": "18754",
  "text": "Our data are in agreement with those showing that IDH wild-type glioblastoma with overexpression of NTRK2 is associated with better OS (p = 0.049; HR: 0.66) [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, NTRK2 was associated with peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor α (PPARα), which was overexpressed and correlated with a good prognosis in IDH wild-type primary glioblastoma [CITATION_2] . CHI3L1 overexpression was associated with mesenchymal subtype in glioblastoma (defined by IDH wild-type) [CITATION_3] .",
